320 Section 2. Section 11-32-2, Code of Alabama 1975, is
321 amended to make conforming changes to read as follows:
322 "§11-32-2
323 As used in this chapter, the following words and
324 phrases shall mean the following unless the context clearly
325 indicates otherwise:
326 (1) AD VALOREM TAX. Those real and personal property ad
327 valorem taxes collected by the county tax collector, the
328 director of revenue of the county, or revenue commissioner, if
329 any, for the county, but shall exclude all ad valorem taxes
330 collected for the State of Alabama and all boards of
331 education, municipalities, fire districts, or other entities
332 located in the county.
333 (2) APPLICANT. A natural person who files a written
334 application with the governing body of any county to which
335 this chapter applies and with a municipality in the county,
336 all in accordance with Section 11-32-3.
Page 12

all in accordance with Section 11-32-3.
