337 (3) AUTHORITY. The public corporation organized
338 pursuant to this chapter, which shall be an agency of the
339 state but shall not be a political subdivision of the state.
340 (4) AUTHORIZING COUNTY. Any county the governing body
341 of which shall have adopted an authorizing resolution, even if
342 the population of the county should fallfalls below 600,000.
343 (5) AUTHORIZING MUNICIPALITY. Any municipality the
344 governing body of which shall have adopted an authorizing
345 resolution.
346 (6) AUTHORIZING RESOLUTION. A resolution, adopted by
